args:
In the blink of an eye, demonic entities swarm
the crowd, and the slaughter of the 666 begins.
As the apostles and angels race to the site,
they find the way blocked by the angel Michael.
Curia of the Ilian Church of Grams\nAugust Cathedral\nAuspecalia Ritual Hall
All of the attendees have arrived,\nYour Eminence—including Her Holiness.
Then everything is ready for the rite.

Yes, Satan will indeed have his offerings.
Oh, but it is close now... So very close.
Everything is within my reach, and soon
it all will be mine!
Yes, and congratulations on all that,\nCardinal! Seizing literally ＂everything＂\nreally is the dream, mmm?
Decided to come after all, eh, Harle?\nWell, I suppose all of your help earns you\na front-row seat for Satan's rebirth.
Harle? ...Ha ha! Oh, that's right! I was\nstill using that name with you, wasn't I?
And what is that supposed to mean?

Oh, nothing of consequence. But truly,
what a momentous occasion this is.
At long last, all of your dreams will
finally be realized.
It has been a struggle—one which took\nfar longer than I initially anticipated.

All the groundwork in the south, placing
people in key positions around the world,
having a backup plan for any possible
contingencies that might arise...

Wait, we had a backup plan? ...Ah, yes!
That matter with the key to perdition.
Was a living descendant of the Goddess
ever truly found?
You're well-informed. Yes, we'd hoped to\nfind a new Scroll of Perdition and access\nmore powerful alchemical recipes.

Those scrolls are teeming with records
of the tools of war from a thousand years
ago—weapons that could greatly aid in
our conquest of South Grastaea.
But in the end, it was merely a way to win\nover some investors. I'll have little use for\nweapons once I command Satan's power.
The Demonlord's might dwarfs even the\nFive Archdemons, and with it I'll become\npope and rule over the world! Aaah ha ha!
Nnngh?! What is that? What's happening?!

Those are the demonic entities born of the
miasma! Stop that at once! You can't just
kill the sacrifices—there is a ritual that
must be followed!
Damned useless creatures. I'll have to\nstop them with the sealing stone...
Impossible... Why aren't they stopping?!\nThey're bound by the sealing stone,\nso why won't they listen?!
AH HA HA HA HA HA HA!
What are you laughing about,\nyou little weasel?!
Oh, but you must forgive me. Your panic\nwas just so delightfully awkward!
Still, if I've offended, let me make it up\nto you with a little secret.
What secret? ...Is this all YOUR treachery?!
You wound me, my friend! This isn't so far\nfrom what you wanted, is it?
Shut your double-crossing mouth, fool!\nYou may have ruined my plans, but I'll\nhave these demonic entities rip you apart!
I rather doubt that; you could pour every\nounce of mana you have into that common\npebble and it won't accomplish a thing.
A common... No! That's not possible!
Oh, but it is. The moment the demon\nwas released from its seal, it became\nno different from any roadside rock.
Basileus! You controlled the demonic\nentities in Rozcimea, remember?!
Use your stone now and purge this traitor!\nHave them tear him limb from limb!
I hate to disappoint, but that won't be\nhappening either. Just like yours,\nBasileus's stone is now devoid of power.
Then how were these entities\neven summoned?!
Well, with the Five Archdemons freed and\nall the sealing stones spent, only a demon\npossessed of miasma can do that.
A demon...? But that means you're—?!
That's right! I'm a demon through\nand through! But you can call me...Loki.
Then the attack on Rozcimea from the\nother day's report was you?
Indeed! That little band of of demonic\nentities—or more properly, miasmic\nangels—was the work of yours truly.
And you knew all along, Basilius?!
What madness is this?! You were willing to\ngive your body to become Satan's vessel!\nYou wanted to fulfill my grand design!
You are a fool. Did you truly believe I\nwould give my life for a scheme born of\nyour staggeringly meager imagination?
I've lived until this day for the purpose\nof taking my vengeance against you.\nWhy would I offer you ANYTHING?

You slaughtered my village just to test
some worthless new weapon—though it
was over a decade ago, so I doubt you
even remember the incident.
You mean that village of heretics?\nYou survived that?
That village you falsely accused of heresy!\nAll so you and the previous Wing of War\ncould play with your sick toys.
And then you burnt what remained to the\nground to destroy the evidence. I've never\nonce forgotten the heat of those flames!
But...but that was all necessary to reach\nthe position I'm in now! Surely you must\nunderstand I had no other choice!
And now you have no choice but to accept\na pathetic death, humiliated and broken.
Don't! Stop this, Basileus! Th-there must\nbe something you want. Say it! Anything!\nWhatever it is, I shall make it yours!
My only wish is revenge for the home\nyou put to the torch...and for his will\nto be granted.
Your floundering has ceased to amuse me,\nand I trust you've had your fill as well.\nIt's time for you to finally be of some use.
We're sure this is the right way?
Yes, Graht and Basileus should be in the\nritual hall just past this... What?!
Hello, Gabriel. Hello, everyone.\nWhere are you off to in such a rush?
As you say, we're in a hurry—so if you try\nto stop us, we won't hold back.
An impressive threat! But sadly, I can't\nstand down until Basileus's grand design\nis brought to fruition.
What grand design? What does he hope to\naccomplish by bringing Satan back to life?

Why do you even ask? Would a persuasive
answer win you over, or will you just
respond with some trite speech on the
emptiness of revenge?
So revenge is what he's after?
Oh, it's not so simple as all that. It's true\nthis will serve as revenge, but it has all\nbecome so much more.
A statement so vague as to be pointless.\nGive an answer with actual substance.
Oh, Sandalphon. Isn't it time you grew a\nbit of a personality? Even androids don't\nsound so mechanical these days.
Well, I suppose some things never change.\nI may not be able to give you the perfect\nanswer, but I can tell you this much...
Basileus's village was wiped out by Graht\nand his own predecessor—the previous\nWing of War.
As I am connected to that Sigil, needless\nto say I was also there when it happened.
But wouldn't that make you another target\nof Basileus's revenge? I never felt that\nsort of hostility between you, but...
It seems I was on his list at one point,\nbut we managed to talk through it\nand reach a kind of accord.

In truth, I was being deceived by Graht
at the time. He told me only that it was a
village of heretics hell-bent on disrupting
the world's order.
Shameful as it is, I had no idea I was\nbeing played for the fool until Basileus\ntold me the truth.
They always took every precaution not to\nbe found out, and I never thought to doubt\nmy own apostle's loyalty.

Still, those are all excuses. Basileus may
have forgiven me after opening my eyes,
but I haven't forgiven myself—which is
why I swore to help him find justice.
Even if what he seeks is ultimately unjust,\nI must atone for my part in that atrocity.
But how do you get from there to reviving\nSatan? That strikes me as the opposite of\ngetting revenge against Graht.
That's the part that isn't so simple. If all\nBasileus wanted was revenge, he could\njust kill Graht and be done with it.
But this has grown beyond one man's\nsearch for vengeance.
I'm confused. Why does a man of \nBasileus's stature need power badly\nenough to resort to such measures?
Afraid I can't share that part. But surely\nit isn't so hard to come up with reasons\na person might seek more power?
Why, just the other day there was a greedy\ncardinal lusting after Satan's power in\norder to rule the world.
Casting aside an absent goddess for a\nnew and very present god and gaining the\nworld in the bargain sounds nice, no?
And Satan's power could make it a reality,\nso Graht planned to destroy the southern\nChurch to command the awe of the people.
Though his was a dream fated to end\nas nothing more than that.
I take it from your tone that Basileus\nhas already claimed his revenge?
Ha ha! Oh, who can tell? Honestly, I\nwouldn't take anything I say too seriously.

That mana... It would seem he does
intend to fight us. But there's no way
he can win—which means he's just
trying to buy time.
I will always be on Basileus's side.\nIf he wished it, I would make an enemy\nof the entire world.
That is my choice—and my atonement.\nSo apologies, my friends, but his dream\ndemands I stop you here!
